<TITLE> Specialist doctor sought to probe BDR suicide cases </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 24 (bdnews24.com)The home ministry has requested for a specialist doctor to probe suicides and other type of unnatural deaths after the Feb 25-26 BDR mutiny, an official said on Sunday. "The committee feels the need of expert medical opinion for appropriate investigation, and so the convener of the committee wrote to the health ministry," the official, who preferred to remain unnamed, told bdnews24.com. Deputy home secretary Md Zakir Hossain, also the convener of the probe committee, sent a letter to the secretary on Thursday night. Following the May 14 circular of the home ministry, a three-member probe committee was formed with the deputy secretary and representatives from police and BDR headquarters. The committee is to submit report on some 20 unnatural deaths including some suicide cases on June 3. bdn
